上一节课回顾：基本定义、语法、常用编辑器（前端开发工具初步了解）

CSS主要作用：美化用HTML构成的页面。HTML仅仅构成Page的框架。
举例：Youtube的样式布局。

接下来，学习利用CSS如何定义布局页面，规划样式。

1.Block elements and inline elements。
	大部分HTML样式以block element和inline element出现。

Block element:每个块级元素都将独占一行。
Example: <p> Paragraph1</p> < p> Paragraph2</p> 
[insert the screenshot]

Inline element: 每个行内元素只占元素自身内容的高度和宽度。
Example: <a href="#">Hypertext Reference1</a> <a href="#"> Hypertext Reference2</a>  
The content will switch to the next line when the current line is full.
<insert the screenshot>


常用block element: <hr> <ol> <p> <div> <ul> <header> <li> <h1>-<h6> <table>
常用的inline element: <a> <textarea> <spam> <img> 

Main diff between block element and inline element:
1.Definition.
2.1 A block element could contain an inline element or a block element.
2.2 A inline could contain as inline element but not contain a block element.

Block: 
1. 填满 Parant Component的Width
2. Width could be specified.
3. Padding(内边距）, margin（外边距） could be specified.

Inline:
1.多个相邻的行内元素排在一行，直到一行拍不下才会换行，其宽度随元素的内容而变化。
2. 设置Width和height没有效果。(在Chrome,IE点击检查，能够查看网页每个部分的长宽)
[screenshot]
3.水平方向的padding和margin才有效果，竖直方向没有效果。
[sreentshot: example of left and right of padding and margin]



Inline-block:
将Block Element以Inline形式出现，但是其他属性保持Block Element.

Div element:
1.Often used a container for other elements.
2.No required attributes, but style, class and id are common.
3.When used together with CSS, the <div> element can be used to style blocks of content.
[Example]

Span element:
1.Often used as a container for inline HTML elements.

NOTE: 
*Both div and span are grouping tags.
*Inspect and available webpage on Internet, massive div and tags could be found most time.

How to change between block and inline element.
1.set display attribute
[Example to make a inline element being a block elements]
[Example to make a block element being a inlie element]
2.set float attribute to div element


How to use CSS
1.External style sheet;(Easy to reuse)
	1.1 Should not contain any HTML tags.
	1.2 must be saved with a .css extension.
	1.3 Dont add a space between the property value and the unit(such as margin-left:20 px;) The right way is : margin-left:20px;(without any spaces between 20 and px)
2.Internal style sheet;(Easy to update and maintain a page)
3.Inline style.(easy to debug for single line, but hard to maintain)


Cascading Order(Priority when collision from high to low )
1.Inline style(inisde an HTML element)
2.External and internal style sheets(in the head section)
	2.1 when both ext and int existing, use the style last defined.
3.Browser default


Example:
In the head section:
.div1{
			border:1px solid red;
			width: 400px;
			height: 200px;
			float:left;
		}
In the body section:
<div class="div1" style="border:5px solid yellow">this is div1</div>


Summary:
1.Block elements and inline elements(definitions, differences)
2.How to use style files(definition, differences, and pros&cons)
3.The rules for style files(The principle of proximity: use the nearest)
